   {:e #blake3 "dcfc4f2a9f7b4fc7475455528ffed70b3010ad69ce177a194c7bfef19ea608f5" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: MaterializedViews.observe_datom is a monoid homomorphism from (P(D), ∪) to the fitness accumulator space. It already maintains 7D F(S) components incrementally at O(1) per datom. But 12 of 13 full O(N) scans in braid status compute values that SHOULD be materialized in the same fold. This task extends observe_datom to maintain ALL derived state, eliminating all batch scans except trace_staleness (filesystem) and frontier_recommendation (embeddings).\n\nALGEBRAIC SPECIFICATION:\nMaterializedViews is a commutative monoid homomorphism:\n  h: (P(D), ∪) → (A₁ × A₂ × ... × Aₖ, ⊕)\nwhere each Aᵢ is a commutative monoid (counters under +, sets under ∪, maps under latest-wins).\n\nThe KEY INVARIANT (generalized SOUND-ISO): For ANY sequence of datoms d₁...dₙ:\n  fold(observe_datom, d₁...dₙ) == batch_compute(∪{d₁...dₙ})\nfor ALL accumulator domains simultaneously.\n\nFOUR NEW ACCUMULATOR DOMAINS:\n\n(A) ISP ENTITY SETS — Currently observe_datom counts ISP datoms but live_projections rescans for entity BTreeSets. Add:\n  isp_intent_entities: HashSet<EntityId>\n  isp_spec_entities: HashSet<EntityId>  \n  isp_impl_entities: HashSet<EntityId>\nOn each Assert, classify by namespace and insert entity. check_coherence_fast reads from views instead of scanning. Phi = |spec_entities \\ impl_covered|.\n\n(B) TASK INDEX — Currently task_open/in_progress/closed count ALL historical assertions (documented as approximate, line 700). Fix: add task_status_live: BTreeMap<EntityId, String>. On :task/status Assert, read previous status from live_view for this (entity, attribute), decrement old counter, insert new status, increment new counter. Gives exact task counts at O(1). Ready set = filter task_status_live by deps (O(tasks), not O(datoms)).\n\n(C) TELEMETRY COUNTERS — telemetry_from_store does 4 separate datoms() scans. Fold into observe_datom:\n  session_count: u64 (increment on :session/status Assert)\n  last_harvest_tx: Option<TxId> (update on :harvest/* attrs)  \n  tx_count: u64 (increment on :tx/provenance-type Assert)\n  task_with_spec_ref_count: u64 (increment on :task/traces-to Assert)\nThese are already partially tracked (harvest_count, observation_count). Complete the set.\n\n(D) INCREMENTAL BETA_1 via Euler Characteristic — beta_1 = |edges| - |vertices| + |components|. Maintain:\n  ref_edge_count: u64 (increment on any Ref-valued Assert)\n  ref_vertex_set: HashSet<EntityId> (insert both source and target of Ref edges)\n  component_count: u64 via Union-Find (decrement when two components merge)\nbeta_1 = ref_edge_count - ref_vertex_set.len() + component_count. O(1) read, O(α(n)) per insert.\n\nIMPLEMENTATION PLAN:\n1. Add all new fields to MaterializedViews struct with Default::default()\n2. Extend observe_datom with classification for each domain\n3. For (B) task index: pass &self.live_view (or accept previous_value as parameter) to do the old-counter-decrement dance\n4. For (D) beta_1: implement Union-Find as a separate struct (UF { parent: Vec<usize>, rank: Vec<usize> }) with find(x) and union(x,y) methods\n5. Add accessor methods: views.isp_projections() -> (LiveView, LiveView, LiveView), views.task_counts_live() -> (u64, u64, u64), views.telemetry() -> SessionTelemetry, views.beta_1() -> u64\n6. Wire check_coherence_fast to use views.isp_projections() and views.beta_1()\n7. Wire telemetry_from_store to delegate to views.telemetry()\n8. Wire task_counts to use views.task_counts_live()\n9. Eliminate live_projections() calls in check_coherence_fast (the function can remain for verification/testing)\n\nACCEPTANCE:\n(A) For ANY sequence of datoms, views.isp_projections() == live_projections(store) (entity sets AND datom counts)\n(B) views.task_counts_live() matches all_tasks(store) grouped by resolved live status for ALL test stores\n(C) views.telemetry() matches telemetry_from_store(store) for ALL fields\n(D) views.beta_1() == compute_beta_1(store) for ALL test stores including cyclic ref graphs\n(E) braid status < 2s at 105K datoms (measure in E2E)\n(F) All 2040+ existing tests pass unchanged\n\nCONSIDERATIONS:\n- The Union-Find for beta_1 is append-only compatible (edges only added, never removed) which matches C1\n- Task index needs the LIVE view to determine previous status. observe_datom currently doesn't have access to live_view. Options: (1) pass &live_view as parameter, (2) store the previous value in a shadow map, (3) accept the current approximate counts and fix them in a post-pass during from_datoms\n- ISP entity sets grow monotonically (append-only, no retractions reduce them). This is guaranteed by C1.\n- The from_datoms path must produce identical MaterializedViews as the incremental path. Both paths must use the same observe_datom callback. Currently from_datoms initializes an empty views and calls observe_datom per datom — this is correct and should be preserved.\n\nFILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs (MaterializedViews struct + observe_datom + accessors), crates/braid-kernel/src/trilateral.rs (wire check_coherence_fast), crates/braid-kernel/src/methodology.rs (wire telemetry_from_store), crates/braid-kernel/src/task.rs (wire task_counts)\nDEPENDS-ON: P6-INDEX-REFACTOR (clean insert path). Supersedes P1-COHERENCE, P2-TASKS, P3-TELEMETRY, P7-VIEWS-ACCURACY." :op :assert}
